casebody.data:
Rayfield BAKER, Petitioner-Appellant, v. Louie L. WAINWRIGHT, Director, Division of Corrections, State of Florida, Respondent-Appellee. No. 72-2169

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 14, 1972.

Before WISDOM, GODBOLD and RONEY, Circuit Judges.

Rule I8, 5 Cir., Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5 Cir., 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Locál Rule 21.1 The appellant has failed to exhaust his state remedies.

. See N.L.R.B. v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir., 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
